{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775863601872,"sessionID":"ses_28649bb73ffezik2O3LE5WmBge","part":{"id":"prt_d79b81a96001z13sivcG10O78W","messageID":"msg_d79b6f26c001i7yRqMSxVYlczl","sessionID":"ses_28649bb73ffezik2O3LE5WmBge","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-6bb3a762c44747c69ae06bea2fa7a887","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-017/design.md","content":"# AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 Design\n\n## Overview\n\n| Item | Value |\n|------|-------|\n| AR | AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件 |\n| Module | `pkg/picod` |\n| Language | Go |\n| Size | S |\n| Stage | ST-1 |\n\nPicoD JWT 中间件提供基于 RSA 公钥的 JWT token 验证机制，用于保护 PicoD 的 `/api/*` 端点。该中间件从环境变量加载公钥，验证请求中的 Bearer token，并将验证结果传递给后续处理器。\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### System Context\n\n```\n┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────┐\n│   Router        │────▶│     PicoD       │────▶│   Sandbox       │\n│ (JWT Token Gen) │     │  (pkg/picod)    │     │ (Execution Env) │\n└─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n        │                       │\n        │                       │\n        ▼                       ▼\n┌─────────────────┐     ┌─────────────────\n│  JWTManager     │     │  AuthManager    │\n│ (Private Key)   │     │  (Public Key)   │\n└─────────────────┘     └─────────────────┘\n```\n\nRouter 使用私钥签发 JWT token，PicoD 使用公钥验证 token。密钥通过 Kubernetes Secret 持久化存储。\n\n### Component Diagram\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                          Server                                  │\n│  ┌───────────┐  ┌──────────────┐  ┌───────────────────────────┐ │\n│  │  Config   │  │ AuthManager  │  │      gin.Engine           │ │\n│  │           │  │              │  │  ┌─────────────────────┐  │ │\n│  │  Port     │  │  publicKey   │  │  │ /health (no auth)   │  │ │\n│  │  Workspace│  │  mutex       │──│──│ /api/* (JWT auth)   │  │ │\n│  └───────────┘  └──────────────┘  │  └─────────────────────┘  │ │\n│                                   │  ┌─────────────────────┐  │ │\n│                                   │  │ Handlers            │  │ │\n│                                   │  │ - ExecuteHandler    │  │ │\n│                                   │  │ - UploadFileHandler │  │ │\n│                                   │  │ - ListFilesHandler  │  │ │\n│                                   │  │ - DownloadFileHandler│  │ │\n│                                   │  └─────────────────────┘  │ │\n│                                   └───────────────────────────┘ │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Request Flow\n\n```\nClient Request (with Authorization: Bearer <token>)\n        │\n        ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 1. Gin Engine Entry                                             │\n│    - Route: /api/*                                              │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 2. AuthMiddleware                                               │\n│    - Extract Authorization header                               │\n│    - Validate \"Bearer \" prefix                                  │\n│    - Extract token string                                       │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 3. JWT Token Parsing                                            │\n│    - jwt.Parse with RSA public key                              │\n│    - Validate signing method (RS256)                            │\n│    - Check expiration (required)                                │\n│    - Check issued-at (required)                                 │\n│    - Apply 1-minute leeway                                      │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 4. Error Classification                                         │\n│    - jwt.ErrTokenExpired → 401 \"token is expired\"              │\n│    - jwt.ErrTokenSignatureInvalid → 401 \"invalid signature\"    │\n│    - invalid signing method → 401 \"invalid signing method\"     │\n│    - other errors → 401 with error message                      │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n        │ (on success)\n        ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 5. Request Body Limit                                           │\n│    - http.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, 32MB)       │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n        │\n        ▼\n┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│ 6. Handler Execution                                            │\n│    - ExecuteHandler, UploadFileHandler, etc.                    │\n└──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### AuthManager (`auth.go`)\n\n```go\ntype AuthManager struct {\n    publicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n    mutex     sync.RWMutex\n}\n\nconst (\n    PublicKeyEnvVar = \"PICOD_AUTH_PUBLIC_KEY\"\n    MaxBodySize     = 32 << 20  // 32 MB\n)\n```\n\n### Server (`server.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Server struct {\n    config      *Config\n    engine      *gin.Engine\n    httpServer  *http.Server\n    authManager *AuthManager\n    workspace   string\n    startTime   time.Time\n}\n\nconst readHeaderTimeout = 10 * time.Second\n```\n\n### Config (`config.go`)\n\n```go\ntype Config struct {\n    Port      int\n    Workspace string\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Endpoints Summary\n\n| Endpoint | Method | Auth | Handler | Description |\n|----------|--------|------|---------|-------------|\n| `/health` | GET | None | `HealthCheckHandler` | Health check endpoint |\n| `/api/execute` | POST | JWT | `ExecuteHandler` | Execute code in sandbox |\n| `/api/files` | POST | JWT | `UploadFileHandler` | Upload file to sandbox |\n| `/api/files` | GET | JWT | `ListFilesHandler` | List files in workspace |\n| `/api/files/*path` | GET | JWT | `DownloadFileHandler` | Download file from sandbox |\n\n### Request Headers\n\n| Header | Required | Format | Description |\n|--------|----------|--------|-------------|\n| `Authorization` | Yes (for /api/*) | `Bearer <token>` | JWT token from Router |\n| `Content-Type` | POST only | `application/json` | Request body format |\n\n### JWT Token Structure\n\n```json\n{\n  \"exp\": <unix timestamp + 5min>,\n  \"iat\": <unix timestamp>,\n  \"iss\": \"agentcube-router\",\n  \"session_id\": \"<session ID>\",\n  \"sandbox_id\": \"<sandbox ID>\",\n  \"namespace\": \"<sandbox namespace>\",\n  \"name\": \"<sandbox name>\"\n}\n```\n\n### Response Format\n\n**Success Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"status\": \"ok\",\n  \"data\": <response data>\n}\n```\n\n**Error Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"error\": \"<error message>\"\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### HTTP Status Codes\n\n| Status | Condition | Error Message |\n|--------|-----------|---------------|\n| 401 | Missing Authorization header | \"missing authorization header\" |\n| 401 | Invalid token format (no Bearer prefix) | \"invalid token format\" |\n| 401 | Token expired | \"token is expired\" |\n| 401 | Invalid signature | \"invalid signature\" |\n| 401 | Wrong signing method | \"invalid signing method\" |\n| 401 | Token invalid (other errors) | `<jwt library error message>` |\n| 401 | Token validation failed | \"invalid token\" |\n\n### Error Response Examples\n\n```json\n// Missing Authorization\n{\"error\": \"missing authorization header\"}\n\n// Token Expired\n{\"error\": \"token is expired\"}\n\n// Invalid Signature\n{\"error\": \"invalid signature\"}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Strategy\n\n1. **Header extraction**: Check Authorization header presence, reject with 401 if missing\n2. **Format validation**: Ensure \"Bearer \" prefix exists, reject with 401 if invalid\n3. **Token parsing**: Use `jwt.Parse` with RSA public key validation\n4. **Expiration check**: Required (`jwt.WithExpirationRequired()`)\n5. **Issued-at check**: Required (`jwt.WithIssuedAt()`)\n6. **Clock skew**: 1-minute leeway (`jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute)`)\n7. **Signing method**: Validate RS256, reject other methods\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n| Test Case | Input | Expected |\n|-----------|-------|----------|\n| `TestNewAuthManager` | Valid PEM public key in env | AuthManager created successfully |\n| `TestNewAuthManagerMissingKey` | No env variable | Error: \"public key environment variable not set\" |\n| `TestNewAuthManagerInvalidPEM` | Invalid PEM data | Error: \"failed to decode PEM block\" |\n| `TestNewAuthManagerWrongKeyType` | Non-RSA key | Error: \"public key is not RSA\" |\n| `TestLoadPublicKeyFromEnv` | Valid RSA PUBLIC KEY PEM | *rsa.PublicKey returned |\n| `TestAuthMiddlewareValidToken` | Valid JWT token | Request continues (200) |\n| `TestAuthMiddlewareMissingHeader` | No Authorization header | 401, \"missing authorization header\" |\n| `TestAuthMiddlewareInvalidFormat` | \"Basic token\" | 401, \"invalid token format\" |\n| `TestAuthMiddlewareExpiredToken` | Expired JWT | 401, \"token is expired\" |\n| `TestAuthMiddlewareInvalidSignature` | Token signed with different key | 401, \"invalid signature\" |\n| `TestAuthMiddlewareWrongSigningMethod` | HS256 signed token | 401, \"invalid signing method\" |\n| `TestAuthMiddlewareEmptyToken` | \"Bearer \" (empty) | 401, error message |\n| `TestSetGetPublicKey` | Set new public key | Get returns new key |\n| `TestPublicKeyConcurrency` | Concurrent Set/Get operations | Thread-safe access |\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n| Scenario | Description |\n|----------|-------------|\n| Full request flow | Valid token → ExecuteHandler invoked |\n| Router-PicoD key sync | Token from Router validated by PicoD |\n| Key rotation | Update public key, new tokens work, old tokens fail |\n| Health endpoint bypass | /health accessible without token |\n\n### Test Patterns\n\n```go\n// Mock JWT token generation for testing\nfunc generateTestToken(claims map[string]interface{}, privateKey *rsa.PrivateKey) string {\n    token := jwt.NewWithClaims(jwt.SigningMethodRS256, jwt.MapClaims(claims))\n    tokenString, _ := token.SignedString(privateKey)\n    return tokenString\n}\n\n// Setup test server with auth middleware\nfunc setupTestServer(authManager *AuthManager) *gin.Engine {\n    engine := gin.New()\n    engine.GET(\"/health\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n        c.JSON(200, gin.H{\"status\": \"ok\"})\n    })\n    api := engine.Group(\"/api\")\n    api.Use(authManager.AuthMiddleware())\n    api.GET(\"/test\", func(c *gin.Context) {\n        c.JSON(200, gin.H{\"status\": \"authenticated\"})\n    })\n    return engine\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## File Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/\n├── auth.go            # AuthManager, JWT validation middleware\n├── auth_test.go       # AuthManager unit tests\n├── config.go          # Server configuration\n├── doc.go             # Package documentation\n├── execute.go         # Code execution handler\n├── files.go           # File upload/download handlers\n├── health.go          # Health check handler\n├── picod_test.go      # Integration tests\n├── sanitize.go        # Input sanitization utilities\n├── server.go          # HTTP server setup and routing\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n| Package | Version | Purpose |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` | v1.10.0 | HTTP router and middleware |\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.2.1 | JWT parsing and validation |\n| `crypto/rsa` | stdlib | RSA public key handling |\n| `crypto/x509` | stdlib | PKIX public key parsing |\n| `encoding/pem` | stdlib | PEM encoding/decoding |\n| `sync` | stdlib | Thread-safe access |\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Notes\n\n### Key Loading\n\n```go\nfunc LoadPublicKeyFromEnv() (*rsa.PublicKey, error) {\n    pemKey := strings.TrimSpace(os.Getenv(PublicKeyEnvVar))\n    if pemKey == \"\" {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"public key environment variable not set\")\n    }\n\n    block, _ := pem.Decode([]byte(pemKey))\n    if block == nil {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"failed to decode PEM block\")\n    }\n\n    if block.Type != \"PUBLIC KEY\" {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"expected PUBLIC KEY PEM block, got %s\", block.Type)\n    }\n\n    pub, err := x509.ParsePKIXPublicKey(block.Bytes)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to parse public key: %w\", err)\n    }\n\n    rsaPub, ok := pub.(*rsa.PublicKey)\n    if !ok {\n        return nil, errors.New(\"public key is not RSA\")\n    }\n\n    return rsaPub, nil\n}\n```\n\n### JWT Validation Options\n\n```go\ntoken, err := jwt.Parse(tokenString, func(token *jwt.Token) (interface{}, error) {\n    if _, ok := token.Method.(*jwt.SigningMethodRSA); !ok {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid signing method\")\n    }\n    return pubKey, nil\n}, jwt.WithExpirationRequired(), jwt.WithIssuedAt(), jwt.WithLeeway(time.Minute))\n```\n\n### Thread-Safe Key Updates\n\n```go\nfunc (a *AuthManager) SetPublicKey(key *rsa.PublicKey) {\n    a.mutex.Lock()\n    a.publicKey = key\n    a.mutex.Unlock()\n}\n\nfunc (a *AuthManager) GetPublicKey() *rsa.PublicKey {\n    a.mutex.RLock()\n    defer a.mutex.RUnlock()\n    return a.publicKey\n}\n```\n\n### Request Body Size Limit\n\n```go\nhttp.MaxBytesReader(c.Writer, c.Request.Body, MaxBodySize)\n```\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- `pkg/router/jwt.go` — JWTManager implementation (token generation)\n- `pkg/router/middleware/auth.go` — Router JWT middleware (reference implementation)\n- `pkg/router/errors.go` — JWT error types (APIStatus interface)\n- `changes/AR-010/design.md` — Router session management design\n- `deployment/client-go.md` — Kubernetes client library reference\n- JWT library: `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5`"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/middleware/auth.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":183,"character":21},"end":{"line":183,"character":32}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/config_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":26,"character":9},"end":{"line":26,"character":9}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field TLSCert"},{"range":{"start":{"line":27,"character":8},"end":{"line":27,"character":8}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field TLSKey"},{"range":{"start":{"line":29,"character":7},"end":{"line":29,"character":7}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/unusedwrite"},"source":"unusedwrite","message":"unused write to field Debug"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/jwt.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":127,"character":53},"end":{"line":127,"character":64}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":145,"character":2},"end":{"line":145,"character":16}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#mapsloop"},"source":"mapsloop","message":"Replace m[k]=v loop with maps.Copy"},{"range":{"start":{"line":234,"character":89},"end":{"line":234,"character":100}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/auth.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":87,"character":63},"end":{"line":87,"character":74}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/server.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/picod/config.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/middleware/auth_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":91,"character":47},"end":{"line":91,"character":58}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":248,"character":47},"end":{"line":248,"character":58}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":383,"character":47},"end":{"line":383,"character":58}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":426,"character":47},"end":{"line":426,"character":58}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/pkg/router/jwt_test.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":61,"character":22},"end":{"line":61,"character":33}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":70,"character":59},"end":{"line":70,"character":70}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":142,"character":47},"end":{"line":142,"character":58}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":174,"character":48},"end":{"line":174,"character":59}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":238,"character":50},"end":{"line":238,"character":61}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":241,"character":59},"end":{"line":241,"character":70}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tool